Meals are now 80% deductible as long as business is discussed. Air fare and lodging are still 100% deductible, as long as there is a planned business meeting in addition to the game. , a Macon, Ga. One big change under the new law limits business-entertainment deductions for tickets to sporting events like the Super Bowl: Only 80% of the face value of such tickets can be deducted. And the companies show few signs of cutting back on their activities despite the new tax law's tighter restrictions on what can be claimed as a business-entertainment expense. 